<plot>Out of Fear is a 21-minute experimental documentary that conveys the personal experiences of five people who have traveled to Australia seeking asylum. Structured as a poetic essay, the film weaves together the stories of their journeys from Sri Lanka, Afghanistan and Iraq, of seeking refuge, of living in detention and of their life after release</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?417992</url></doc>
